WEBVTT

00:01.702 --> 00:23.001
In late 1987 and in 1988, there was a great deal of 
excitement in the House of South Texas area about

00:01.702 --> 00:23.001
the expansion of higher education in South Texas 
and the further development of

00:25.428 --> 00:31.517
this area with regards to institutions of higher 
education. There was no question that South Texas

00:33.139 --> 00:39.869
had been neglected with regards to higher 
education. And the legislators in South Texas

00:41.292 --> 00:53.730
placed the blame at the feet of the legislature as a 
whole. The truth of the matter is that the

00:54.757 --> 01:03.869
legislature responds to requests that are made by 
individual legislators. Not that they always get

01:04.710 --> 01:09.156
what they ask for, but they first have to ask for it. 
Now Texas, by 1987, had emerged from the old

01:10.718 --> 01:24.696
patrone system that really had little regard for 
higher education for its masses. and most of the

01:26.093 --> 01:31.039
legislators responded accordingly. I recall one 
time in earlier years when I was serving in the

01:32.540 --> 01:55.847
legislature, this was about 1974 as I can best 
remember, I struck up a conversation with the

01:32.540 --> 01:55.847
state representative from Duval County one day 
and I stated that I see that he has an opponent in the

01:57.177 --> 02:04.584
election.

02:07.866 --> 02:12.631
And he was devoting some time to campaigning. Let 
me know very quickly that he did not have to

02:14.072 --> 02:26.543
campaign, that George Parr elected him, and see to 
it that he was reelected. This particular state

02:26.962 --> 02:40.470
representative at that time had I'm sure no 
interest in promoting higher education in South

02:26.962 --> 02:40.470
Texas.

02:40.510 --> 02:46.202
In 87 and 88 all of this had changed with the 
election of a new generation of legislators that

02:48.275 --> 02:59.585
were no longer under the control of certain 
politically powerful individuals. This is not to

03:00.746 --> 03:15.700
suggest that all state representatives and 
senators in South Texas were under anyone's

03:00.746 --> 03:15.700
person's control, such as George Parr, is simply 
to point out that there was that environment in

03:16.372 --> 03:29.272
South Texas

03:16.372 --> 03:29.272
in the earlier years and prior years. We began to 
think about what we would be proposing to the joint

03:30.574 --> 03:43.695
committee that was established to look at higher 
education in South Texas. We came to certain

03:44.755 --> 04:00.711
conclusions, but recognized the fact that the 
University of Texas system would need to be

03:44.755 --> 04:00.711
conferred with on all these matters. There were 
essentially five institutions, three that

04:01.872 --> 04:10.881
existed within the University of South Texas 
system.

