i.e., Corpus Christi State University, Texas A&I 
University in Kingsville, and Laredo State

04:14.320 --> 04:26.539
University in Laredo. In Edinburgh, Texas, there 
was Pan American University with a branch in

04:28.402 --> 04:35.232
Brownsville. that was strictly an upper-level 
institution and located on the Junior College

04:36.224 --> 04:45.409
campus in Brownsville, Texas. Our initial 
meeting with the University of Texas System

04:46.853 --> 04:52.107
Chancellor that they were interested in Pan 
American University at Edinburgh with its branch

04:53.572 --> 05:17.638
in Brownsville and Laredo State University 
becoming a part of the University of Texas system

04:53.572 --> 05:17.638
and leaving the Texas A&M University system with 
Corpus Christi State University and Texas A&I

04:53.572 --> 05:17.638
University. in Laredo State University was 
because of the fact they had University of Texas at

05:18.479 --> 05:46.512
El Paso on the border to the west and would have Pan 
